node.text: The 4th trimester has been a journey & I know everyone has a different relationship with it. Going to be 4 months into this part of the journey soon. Aiming to do at least a year of breastfeeding. So many have told me I’d drop the baby weight in this time - instead I’ve gained. I’m okay with my body & what it’s going through, but I’ve had my moments. Being 5’3 & 160+ lbs things sit differently & while some people celebrate the thickness, not everyone does. I’ve had comments from people I know that weren’t so nice, accompanied by being touched without consent. This is a part of womanhood I have never felt safe in, my body being off limits to others unless I say so. From being sexualized as a child through comments made by adults, to being touched without my consent as I got older. It’s really wild how no matter how much you’ve healed- parenthood will remind you of what you had to heal from, to avoid your child needing to do the same. It’s why I will not tolerate people who are unkind, inappropriate in many ways & do not honor consent influencing my child. It’s why I won’t tolerate any out of pocket behavior or actions being done to my child either. My parents did their best with what they knew of at the time etc- but now I know better in many ways. I will be kicking ass & taking names. So that my child doesn’t have to. Funniest part of it all? My baby has been the EASIEST part of this- it’s been dealing with adults that has been the most difficult.

node.text:
🌻🌺& the category is body🌺🌻

Instead of pressing people who are postpartum to “SnapBack” why not insure they are supported in healing? That their uterus has shrunk back & is where it needs to be? That their ab muscles are back where they need to be? Those are just two of the things- there’s really so much more but let’s start with that.
